cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.SI 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it deals with the puzzle of overfitting in deep neural networks and proposes a solution based on the analysis of the dynamical system corresponding to gradient descent of a multilayer network. It may also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it deals with deep neural networks. Additionally, it may be relevant to the sub-categories of cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as deep neural networks are widely used in these fields. Finally, it may also be relevant to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as deep neural networks are used in various applications related to social networks and information networks.
